**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Attackers can attempt unlimited passwords against any account
- Credential stuffing attacks using leaked password databases are trivial
- Automated tools like Hydra, Burp Suite, or custom scripts can test thousands of credentials per minute
- No visibility into ongoing attacks - no alerts or logging of suspicious activity

**SECURE VERSION**:

```java
import java.sql.*;
import java.time.Instant;
import java.time.Duration;
import javax.servlet.http.*;
import org.mindrot.jbcrypt.BCrypt;
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;

public class SecureLoginServlet extends HttpServlet {
    private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(SecureLoginServlet.class);
    private static final String DB_URL = "jdbc:postgresql://localhost/userdb";
    private static final String DB_USER = "appuser";
    private static final String DB_PASS = "dbpassword";

    private static final int MAX_FAILED_ATTEMPTS = 5;
    private static final int LOCKOUT_DURATION_MINUTES = 15;

    @Override
    protected void doPost(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response) {
        String username = request.getParameter("username");
        String password = request.getParameter("password");
        String clientIP = request.getRemoteAddr();

        try (Connection conn = DriverManager.getConnection(DB_URL, DB_USER, DB_PASS)) {
            // Check if account is locked
            if (isAccountLocked(conn, username)) {
                logger.warn("Login attempt on locked account: {} from IP: {}", username, clientIP);
                response.sendRedirect("/login?error=locked");
                return;
            }

            String sql = "SELECT id, password_hash, failed_attempts, locked_until FROM users WHERE username = ?";
            PreparedStatement stmt = conn.prepareStatement(sql);
            stmt.setString(1, username);
            ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();

            if (rs.next()) {
                String storedHash = rs.getString("password_hash");
                int userId = rs.getInt("id");

                if (BCrypt.checkpw(password, storedHash)) {
                    // SUCCESS: Reset failed attempts and create session
                    resetFailedAttempts(conn, userId);
                    logger.info("Successful login for user: {} from IP: {}", username, clientIP);

                    HttpSession session = request.getSession(true);
                    session.setAttribute("username", username);
                    session.setAttribute("userId", userId);
                    response.sendRedirect("/dashboard");
                } else {
                    // FAILURE: Increment failed attempts, possibly lock account
                    int newFailedCount = incrementFailedAttempts(conn, userId);
                    logger.warn("Failed login attempt {} for user: {} from IP: {}", 
                               newFailedCount, username, clientIP);

                    if (newFailedCount >= MAX_FAILED_ATTEMPTS) {
                        lockAccount(conn, userId);
                        logger.error("Account locked due to {} failed attempts: {} from IP: {}", 
                                    newFailedCount, username, clientIP);
                    }
                    response.sendRedirect("/login?error=invalid");
                }
            } else {
                // User not found - use constant time to prevent enumeration
                BCrypt.checkpw(password, "$2a$10$dummy.hash.to.prevent.timing.attacks");
                logger.warn("Login attempt for non-existent user: {} from IP: {}", username, clientIP);
                response.sendRedirect("/login?error=invalid");
            }
        } catch (SQLException e) {
            logger.error("Database error during login", e);
            response.sendRedirect("/login?error=system");
        }
    }

    private boolean isAccountLocked(Connection conn, String username) throws SQLException {
        String sql = "SELECT locked_until FROM users WHERE username = ?";
        PreparedStatement stmt = conn.prepareStatement(sql);
        stmt.setString(1, username);
        ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();

        if (rs.next()) {
            Timestamp lockedUntil = rs.getTimestamp("locked_until");
            if (lockedUntil != null && lockedUntil.toInstant().isAfter(Instant.now())) {
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }

    private int incrementFailedAttempts(Connection conn, int userId) throws SQLException {
        String sql = "UPDATE users SET failed_attempts = failed_attempts + 1 WHERE id = ? RETURNING failed_attempts";
        PreparedStatement stmt = conn.prepareStatement(sql);
        stmt.setInt(1, userId);
        ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();
        return rs.next() ? rs.getInt(1) : 0;
    }

    private void lockAccount(Connection conn, int userId) throws SQLException {
        String sql = "UPDATE users SET locked_until = ? WHERE id = ?";
        PreparedStatement stmt = conn.prepareStatement(sql);
        stmt.setTimestamp(1, Timestamp.from(Instant.now().plus(Duration.ofMinutes(LOCKOUT_DURATION_MINUTES))));
        stmt.setInt(2, userId);
        stmt.executeUpdate();
    }

    private void resetFailedAttempts(Connection conn, int userId) throws SQLException {
        String sql = "UPDATE users SET failed_attempts = 0, locked_until = NULL WHERE id = ?";
        PreparedStatement stmt = conn.prepareStatement(sql);
        stmt.setInt(1, userId);
        stmt.executeUpdate();
    }
}
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **Account lockout after 5 failed attempts**: Prevents brute force attacks by temporarily disabling login after threshold
- **Time-based lockout (15 minutes)**: Automatic unlock prevents permanent DoS while still blocking attackers
- **Failed attempt tracking per account**: Tracks and stores failed attempts in database for persistence across server restarts
- **Comprehensive logging**: All login attempts logged with username and IP for security monitoring and forensics

